          Dlaczego nasze strony <span class="text-accent">działają</span>?
        </h2>
        <p class="text-lg text-muted max-w-2xl mx-auto">
          Każda strona internetowa to przemyślany projekt łączący estetykę z funkcjonalnością i technologią.
        </p>
      </div>
      
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
        {features.map((feature, index) => (
          <div class="group p-6 rounded-2xl border border-theme bg-card hover:border-accent/50 transition-all duration-300 animate-on-scroll" style={`animation-delay: ${index * 100}ms`}>
            <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-xl bg-accent/10 flex items-center justify-center mb-4 group-hover:bg-accent/20 transition-colors">
              {feature.icon === 'responsive' && (
                <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-accent" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                  <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 18h.01M8 21h8a2 2 0 002-2V5a2 2 0 00-2-2H8a2 2 0 00-2 2v14a2 2 0 002 2z"/>
                </svg>
              )}
              {feature.icon === 'speed' && (
                <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-accent" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                  <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M13 10V3L4 14h7v7l9-11h-7z"/>
                </svg>
              )}
